    <h1>
     Glass Tube
    </h1>
    <h3>
     Source
    </h3>
    <text><style color="0xaaaaaa" italic="true">Note: this page is ported from MCMOD's GTCEu wiki.<br/>Author: <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/179043/">花海</style>, <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/Yefancy">KilaBash</style><br/></style></text>
    <text>
        Glass tubes, made from glass dust in <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:machines/forming_press" hover-info="click link">Forming Press</style> or <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:machines/alloy_smelter" hover-info="click link">Alloy smelter</style>, 
        or from glass liquid in a <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:machines/fluid_solidifier" hover-info="click link">Fluid Solidifier</style> with a <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:misc/mold" hover-info="click link">casting mold (ball)</style>, 
        consume 1 glass material for every 1 glass tube produced. Glass tubes can be made with only LV voltage.
        <br/>
        <br/>
        Glass tubes can be used to craft <style color="0xafff00" underlined="true" link="gtceu:circuits/vacuum_tube" hover-info="click link">Vacuum Tubes</style>, a primary component of your first circuit.
    </text>
